"Never Let You Go" was performed seventeenth on the night (following Ukraine's Olexandr Ponomariov with "" and preceding Norway's Jostein Hasselgård with ""). For her Eurovision appearance, Mando wore a navy blue gown, with a very tight lace-up bodice. She also had several backup dancers. At the close of voting, it had received 25 points, placing 17th in a field of 26.

It was succeeded as Greek representative at the 2004 Contest by Sakis Rouvas with "Shake It".







